excerpt: Family-friendly water park with go-karts, mini-golf, an arcade, laser tag & a climbing wall.
detail_description: Daytona Lagoon is a family-friendly water park and entertainment center located just north of the pier area and steps from the beach. It offers a variety of attractions, including go-karts, mini-golf, an arcade, laser tag, and a climbing wall. The Speedway Indoor Karting features state-of-the-art electric-powered karts on a 16-turn road course with multiple elevation changes. In 2019, Daytona Lagoon completed $1.
name: Daytona Lagoon
address: 601 Earl St, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

excerpt: Long-standing venue on a nature preserve with global art, Florida history exhibits & a planetarium.
detail_description: The Museum of Arts & Sciences, located on a 90-acre nature preserve in Florida, is a long-standing venue that offers a diverse range of exhibits and attractions. Visitors can explore global art, Florida history exhibits, and a state-of-the-art planetarium.
name: Museum of Arts & Sciences
address: 352 S Nova Rd, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

excerpt: Home of the Daytona 500, this track also features tours & interactive race car attractions.
detail_description: Daytona International Speedway, known as the 'World Center of Racing,' is a must-visit destination in Daytona Beach. It's home to the famous Daytona 500 and offers tours and interactive race car attractions. The area also boasts a diverse range of accommodations, from luxurious resorts to budget-friendly options. Visitors can enjoy outdoor adventures, family-friendly attractions, arts and cultural venues, and a vibrant culinary scene beyond the beach.
name: Daytona International Speedway
address: 1801 W International Speedway Blvd, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

excerpt: Airy museum featuring a huge collection of Florida-themed paintings, plus a gift shop & cafe.
detail_description: The Cici and Hyatt Brown Museum of Art is a beautiful art museum in Daytona Beach, Florida that features a large collection of paintings related to the state. The museum has a modern feel with high ceilings and vaults, and is home to thousands of pieces of art from around the country.
name: Cici and Hyatt Brown Museum of Art
address: 352 S Nova Rd, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

excerpt: This wooden pier stretches from the boardwalk into the ocean & features a seafood restaurant.
detail_description: Daytona Beach Main Street Pier is a historic 1,000-foot wooden pier that has been a bustling hub of activity since 1925. Despite enduring multiple hurricanes and tropical storms, the pier received a $1.56 million makeover in 2023 to ensure its longevity for years to come. At the end of Main Street, visitors can explore the lively Daytona Beach Boardwalk & Pier, lined with restaurants, bars, an arcade, bait shop, and souvenir shops.
name: Daytona Beach Main Street Pier
address: 1200 Main St Bridge, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

excerpt: Daytona Beach is a city on Florida’s Atlantic coast. It’s known for Daytona International Speedway, which hosts February’s iconic Daytona 500 NASCAR race. The beach has hard-packed sand where driving is permitted in designated areas. Near the boardwalk’s rides and arcades, Daytona Beach Bandshell stages free summer concerts. Steps from the beach, Daytona Lagoon water park offers go-karts, laser tag and waterslides.
detail_description: Daytona Beach, located on Florida's Atlantic coast, is famous for hosting the iconic Daytona 500 NASCAR race at the Daytona International Speedway. The beach allows driving in designated areas with hard-packed sand and offers a lively boardwalk with rides and free summer concerts at the Daytona Beach Bandshell. Nearby, visitors can enjoy go-karts, laser tag, and waterslides at the Daytona Lagoon water park.
name: Daytona Beach
address: Florida, USA

excerpt: Beachfront rides, games & other attractions (such as summer concerts) in a carnival-like atmosphere.
detail_description: Daytona Boardwalk Amusements, also known as the "Broadwalk," is a vibrant beachfront area that offers a carnival-like atmosphere with various attractions for visitors of all ages. Established in 1938 and continuously renovated, it features an array of activities including rides, games, free concerts, shops, and dining options.
name: Daytona Boardwalk Amusements
address: 12 N Ocean Ave., Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

excerpt: This historic ballpark is home to the Daytona Cubs & the site of the first integrated baseball game.
detail_description: Jackie Robinson Ballpark, located on City Island in Daytona Beach, is a historic minor league baseball park and museum. It holds significance as the site of the first integrated baseball game and is named after the legendary African-American baseball player Jackie Robinson. Visitors can enjoy watching the Daytona Tortugas play while learning about the history of racial injustice in sports. The ballpark offers various promotions such as Taco Tuesdays and Thirsty Thursdays, making it a great stop for families and sports enthusiasts alike.
name: Jackie Robinson Ballpark
address: 105 E Orange Ave, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

excerpt: Airy, simple shop offering a range of housemade confections, with tours of the on-site factory.
detail_description: Located in Daytona Beach, Florida, Angell & Phelps Chocolate Factory is a delightful destination for chocolate lovers. Established in 1925 and using original recipes, the factory offers free guided tours where visitors can witness the chocolate-making process and indulge in complimentary samples. The company's unique chocolate products come in various shapes such as alligators, conch shells, dolphins, and sand dollars. A visit to this charming factory promises a sweet experience for both children and adults alike.
name: Angell & Phelps Chocolate Factory
address: 154 S Beach St, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

detail_description: Lilian Place Heritage Center, a historic house dating back to 1884, was acquired by the Heritage Preservation Trust in 2009. It stands as the oldest home on Daytona Beach's beachside and offers guided tours from Wednesday to Monday. The center also hosts various events like the Wednesday Winedown and Victorian Tea. This charming house is a prime example of High Victorian architecture with its high ceilings and solid pine floors.
name: Lilian Place Heritage Center
address: 1000 S Peninsula Dr, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

excerpt: Adventure-themed mini-golf course with waterfalls, gator feedings, scavenger hunts & arcade games.
detail_description: Congo River Golf is an adventure-themed mini-golf course that offers much more than just golf. With 18 award-winning miniature golf courses, guests can enjoy cave exploration, waterfalls, and even a gator exhibit where they can feed live gators. The course is filled with exciting features such as caves, rainforests, and rocky summits. It's a great activity for both experienced mini-golfers and beginners looking for a fun challenge.
name: Congo River Golf
address: 2100 S Atlantic Ave, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

excerpt: Circa-1937 amphitheater on the boardwalk with a seasonal lineup of live concerts.
detail_description: The Daytona Beach Bandshell is a historic amphitheater built in 1937, located on the lively boardwalk of Daytona Beach. It hosts a variety of live concerts, festivals, and cultural events throughout the year, making it a focal point for entertainment in this coastal city. Visitors can enjoy music performances while lounging on the nearby beach or immerse themselves in the vibrant arts scene of the area.
name: Daytona Beach Bandshell
address: 70 Boardwalk, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

excerpt: Scenic golf club featuring two 18-hole courses, a pool & a fitness center, plus a bar & grill.
detail_description: LPGA International is a picturesque golf club in Daytona Beach, known for its two 18-hole courses, as well as amenities like a pool and fitness center. The area is famous for being the headquarters of LPGA and NASCAR, and it's home to the renowned Daytona International Speedway. With a wide range of accommodations available, from luxurious resorts to budget-friendly options, there's something for every traveler.
name: LPGA International
address: 1000 Champions Dr, Daytona Beach, FL 32124, USA

excerpt: Thrill ride on Daytona Beach boardwalk propelling riders more than 360 ft. at about 100 mph.
detail_description: Located at Screamers Park near Daytona Beach's Main Street Pier, the Daytona SlingShot is a thrilling ride that propels riders over 360 feet into the air at speeds of about 100 mph. Alongside this adrenaline-pumping experience, visitors can also enjoy the Vomatron, a ride with seats at the end of a massive 165-foot arm. Both rides have no weight or age limits, making them accessible to all thrill-seekers.
name: Daytona Sling Shot
address: 25 S Atlantic Ave, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

detail_description: The Daytona Ice Arena, situated in South Daytona, is a modern ice skating facility that offers various activities such as recreational ice skating, figure skating, and speed skating. It features a National Hockey League sized rink and provides adult and youth lessons for both ice skating and hockey. The arena hosts daily public skate sessions suitable for all ages and skill levels. Whether you're an experienced skater or just starting out, the Daytona Ice Arena promises an exhilarating experience on the ice.
name: Daytona Ice Arena
address: 2400 S Ridgewood Ave #63d, South Daytona, FL 32119, USA

excerpt: Spacious 1949 venue hosting a variety of music, comedy, dance & Broadway theater shows.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Daytona Beach, the Peabody Auditorium stands as a testament to the rich cultural tapestry of this coastal city. Since its inception in 1949, this spacious venue has become a beloved hub for an eclectic mix of performances, including music concerts, comedy acts, dance showcases, and Broadway productions.
name: Peabody Auditorium
address: 600 Auditorium Blvd, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

excerpt: Lively hangout by the Loggerhead Marina furnishing live music & Caribbean-inspired eats &  drinks.
detail_description: Caribbean Jack's is a lively waterfront hangout located at the Loggerhead Marina in Daytona Beach. It's a popular spot for both locals and tourists, offering Caribbean-inspired cuisine such as Crabby Patties and Gator Bites, along with specialty tropical drinks and shareable desserts. The restaurant provides indoor and outdoor seating with scenic views of the Intracoastal Waterway. Guests can enjoy live music on the outdoor deck while dining on fresh seafood and regional Florida favorites.
name: Caribbean Jack's
address: 721 Ballough Rd, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

excerpt: This 4-acre park features a seasonal interactive splash pad, walkways & a covered playground.
detail_description: Sun Splash Park is a delightful four-acre oceanfront oasis located on South Atlantic Avenue, perfect for families and beachgoers alike. This vibrant park boasts a state-of-the-art 3,500-square-foot splash pad that features an impressive array of 42 water jets shooting refreshing streams up to six feet high. The colorful play surface offers stunning views of the Atlantic Ocean, making it an ideal spot for kids to cool off and have fun.
name: Sun Splash Park
address: 611 S Atlantic Ave, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA

detail_description: The Motorsports Hall of Fame of America is a 10,000 square foot facility located within the Daytona International Speedway. It showcases an impressive collection honoring various forms of motorsports, including stock cars, sports cars, open-wheel vehicles, motorcycles, drag racing, land speed records, powerboating and aviation.
name: Motorsports Hall of Fame of America
address: 1801 W International Speedway Blvd, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

detail_description: Boardwalk Main St. Pier is a vibrant destination offering a variety of activities for visitors. Take in the scenic views, rent bicycles, and explore historic sites nearby. The walkway, though not made of wood like a traditional boardwalk, provides a pleasant stroll with its paver construction. Enjoy the thrill of visiting the Main Street Pier and indulge in some classic arcade games at reasonable prices.
name: Boardwalk Main St. Pier
address: Main St Bridge, Daytona Beach, FL 32118, USA
